OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBank economist sorry for   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25F'you're poorer' remark     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The Bank of England's top economist has
OL,6, said he is sorry for using             
OL,7, "inflammatory" language to suggest     
OL,8, people must accept they are poorer.    
OL,10,FHuw Pill recently said people needed to
OL,11,Fstop asking for pay rises to keep up   
OL,12,Fwith soaring prices because this risked
OL,13,Fkeeping inflation higher for longer.   
OL,15,FHowever, his remarks prompted          
OL,16,Fcriticism, including from his own boss.
OL,18,FBank of England governor Andrew Bailey 
OL,19,Fsaid Mr Pill's "choice of words was not
OL,20,Fright".                                
